NiftyObject.name: Machine Hallucinations - Mars - F #1/42
NiftyObject.description: Comes with a physical print! ''17 x ''22 inches. NFT must be owned at the time of shipping to receive the print.

contractObj.storeName: Machine Hallucinations ‚Äì Mars : AI Data Paintings by Refik Anadol
contractObj.storeDescription:
Refik Anadol (b. 1985, Istanbul, Turkey) is a media artist, director and pioneer in the aesthetics of data and machine intelligence. His body of work locates creativity at the intersection of humans and machines. In taking the data that flows around us as the primary material and the neural network of a computerized mind as a collaborator, Anadol paints with a thinking brush, offering us radical visualizations of our digitized memories and expanding the possibilities of architecture, narrative, and the body in motion. 
 Anadol‚Äôs site-specific AI data sculptures, live audio/visual performances, and immersive installations take many forms, while encouraging us to rethink our engagement with the physical world, its temporal and spatial dimensions, and the creative potential of machines. Machine Hallucinations ‚Äì Mars : AI Data Paintings offer a new kind of cognitive cartography for data universes by using a neural network trained on 1.5 million archival photographic memories of HiRISE telescope of MRO Mars. A poetic journey in the mind of a machine explores vast synthetic landscapes of Mars to image a space yet reachable by humans. 
 Providing imaginary texture to this still unfamiliar place, Machine Hallucinations ‚Äì Mars : AI Data Paintings illustrates a dreamscape of possible futures and hidden pasts. These machine-hallucinated AI Data Paintings come to represent collective memory, hidden layers of history, and then consciousness of a planet that, otherwise, might remain unseen. 
 HiRISE (High Resolution Imaging Science Experiment) is the most powerful camera ever sent to another planet, one of six instruments onboard the Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter. It was launched in 2005, arrived at Mars in 2006, and have been imaging ever since. MRO's camera‚Äôs high resolution capability (imaging up to 30 centimeters per pixel) remains unprecedented for any existing orbiter in the study of the Red Planet, as well as being an indispensable instrument for helping to select landing sites for robotic and future human exploration. 
 Resolution : 10200 x 13200PX. Generated from 32Bit EXR format. 
 EACH OPEN EDITION COMES WITH A PHYSICAL PRINT! ''17 x ''22 inches.
contractObj.storeDescription2: Refik Anadol is one the most successful AI artists in the world. He relies heavily on AI technology to create his work - the result is some of the most surreal and beautiful artworks you can possibly find. This has led to Refik being featured in exhibitions around the world while receiving countless awards along the way. These include, but are not limited to, GQ Turkey Man of the Year (2019) and Lumen Gold Prize - Melting Memories (2019). We are honored to feature Refik's work on Nifty Gateway - it is a huge moment for our platform and the NFT space.
contractObj.storeHeadline: Refik Anadol releases 5 minute open editions!

NiftyObject.project_name: THE SECOND STORM Open by Justin Maller
NiftyObject.name: CLOSE

contractObj.storeName: THE SECOND STORM Open by Justin Maller
contractObj.storeDescription:
A pioneer in the digital art world, Justin Maller has been creating work at the juncture of avant garde and pop culture since the turn of the century. Maller has had a celebrated career pushing the boundaries of the digital medium as an independent artist. Since founding seminal art collective Depthcore in 2002, he has created work for clients including Nike, Gatorade, The Grammys, Dolby, LG, Jordan and Under Armour. Building on this success, Maller‚Äôs groundbreaking, year-long project ‚ÄòFacets‚Äô forged an iconic brand cemented in his trademark geometric approach. This style has had a visible and lasting influence on visual art practice around the world. 
 - 
 Artist's Statement 
 I created the majority of ‚ÄúThe Second Storm‚Äù in Australian hotel quarantine, after flying from Los Angeles to see my mother at the end of her battle with cancer. I was escorted by the military from the airport to a hotel room where I would spend two weeks alone in confinement. Around the same time I landed, mum checked in to hospital for the last time. 
  I spent those two weeks creating this artwork as I sought to come to terms. To terms with mums life ending. To terms with being locked in a room with so little time left. To terms with life and death and grief and love and everything in between.
contractObj.storeDescription2: We're thrilled to welcome Justin Maller to Nifty Gateway! He is a true OG in the digital art scene having been around for well over 20 years. We could not be more excited to host him for his first even tokenized collection. We also love the amount of emotion and passion Justin put into this collection and this is easy to see in the final artworks.
contractObj.storeHeadline: Justin Maller releases 5 minute open editions!

NiftyObject.project_name: Art of Resistance II Packs by PR1MAL CYPHER
NiftyObject.name: Edward Snowden #22/25

contractObj.storeName: Art of Resistance II Packs by PR1MAL CYPHER
contractObj.storeDescription: PR1MAL CYPHER studied philosophy, linguistics, psychoanalysis and art in Innsbruck and Vienna. In the past his artistic work was mainly in the field of oil painting. At the beginning of 2020 he reinvented himself and forced himself in his work mainly into the digital field and especially into the crypto art and NFT scene, in which he quickly flourished and gained a wider recognition. PR1MAL CYPHER was born. His work is largely inspired by the Vaporwave and Outrun art, as his passion has been CYBERPUNK since his early youth. He sees in it not only a graceful aesthetic. Cyberpunk is much more‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääa bridge of the present and its technical innovations and ambitions to different scenarios of the future of mankind, which will be significantly influenced by technology. The reference to the Cypherpunk, Anonymous and also Blockchain movement is thus clearly reflected in his works and is of crucial importance. Welcome back to the second part of the "ART OF RESISTANCE" series, which actually accompany a multi-part article series published in Bitcoin Magazine. This second collection is a preview of the soon to be published articles and features a rich array of different works that have been kept low in terms of limitation, which is why the most circulated artworks have only 25 editions. As in the first part of the series, the special "Hackers Green Editions" have only 10 editions per Cypherpunk portrait and even less as far as the other images are concerned.
contractObj.storeDescription2: PR1MAL CYPHER currently is one of the few crypto artists to mainly use a neon color scheme. Since he has began tokenizing his artwork, he has become recognizable for this color scheme and it has evolved into his brand. The neon artwork pops of the screen with vibrant colors and beautiful details.
contractObj.storeHeadline: Pr1mal Cypher releases follow up Art of Resistance packs!

contractObj.storeDescription: Joanie Lemercier is a French visual artist working primarily with light in space, and its influence on our perception. As one of the pioneers of projection mapping, he‚Äôs been doing architectural projections around the world since 2005, and performed in music festivals such as Mutek (Montreal, Mexico), Sonar (Barcelona), Unsound (Poland), Decibel (Seattle), Flying Tokyo (Japan) and co-created Flying Lotus‚Äô show at the Roundhouse in London. \n\n Since 2010, he is represented by Art galleries in NYC, Paris and Brussels, and Lemercier's physical artworks, combining print and light projections are often shown in Art fairs. In 2013, he collaborated with Jay-Z to create the holidays windows for Barneys flagship store on Madison avenue in NYC. His work has been exhibited at China Museum of Digital Art (Beijing), Sundance film festival and Art Basel Miami. Today, he runs his Art studio in Brussels, Belgium, and starts exploring the Crypto Art space as a new way to distribute his bright geometric compositions.
contractObj.storeDescription2: Joanie Lemercier is an absolute expert in lighting and projection mapping. He has created some of the most impressive projection mapping displays ever, leading to him putting on shows at several festivals and art fairs across the world. These displays captivate and astound viewers - we expected his NFT collection to be no different. The final product was exactly what we expected - a brilliant collection of 6 artworks of the highest quality. Welcome to NG Joanie!
contractObj.storeHeadline: Renowned visual artist and projection mapping pioneer Joanie Lemercier releases debut NG collection!

contractObj.storeName: Machine Hallucinations ‚Äì Mars : AI Data Paintings by Refik Anadol
contractObj.storeDescription:
Refik Anadol (b. 1985, Istanbul, Turkey) is a media artist, director and pioneer in the aesthetics of data and machine intelligence. His body of work locates creativity at the intersection of humans and machines. In taking the data that flows around us as the primary material and the neural network of a computerized mind as a collaborator, Anadol paints with a thinking brush, offering us radical visualizations of our digitized memories and expanding the possibilities of architecture, narrative, and the body in motion. 
 Anadol‚Äôs site-specific AI data sculptures, live audio/visual performances, and immersive installations take many forms, while encouraging us to rethink our engagement with the physical world, its temporal and spatial dimensions, and the creative potential of machines. Machine Hallucinations ‚Äì Mars : AI Data Paintings offer a new kind of cognitive cartography for data universes by using a neural network trained on 1.5 million archival photographic memories of HiRISE telescope of MRO Mars. A poetic journey in the mind of a machine explores vast synthetic landscapes of Mars to image a space yet reachable by humans. 
 Providing imaginary texture to this still unfamiliar place, Machine Hallucinations ‚Äì Mars : AI Data Paintings illustrates a dreamscape of possible futures and hidden pasts. These machine-hallucinated AI Data Paintings come to represent collective memory, hidden layers of history, and then consciousness of a planet that, otherwise, might remain unseen. 
 HiRISE (High Resolution Imaging Science Experiment) is the most powerful camera ever sent to another planet, one of six instruments onboard the Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter. It was launched in 2005, arrived at Mars in 2006, and have been imaging ever since. MRO's camera‚Äôs high resolution capability (imaging up to 30 centimeters per pixel) remains unprecedented for any existing orbiter in the study of the Red Planet, as well as being an indispensable instrument for helping to select landing sites for robotic and future human exploration. 
 Resolution : 10200 x 13200PX. Generated from 32Bit EXR format. 
 EACH OPEN EDITION COMES WITH A PHYSICAL PRINT! ''17 x ''22 inches.
contractObj.storeDescription2: Refik Anadol is one the most successful AI artists in the world. He relies heavily on AI technology to create his work - the result is some of the most surreal and beautiful artworks you can possibly find. This has led to Refik being featured in exhibitions around the world while receiving countless awards along the way. These include, but are not limited to, GQ Turkey Man of the Year (2019) and Lumen Gold Prize - Melting Memories (2019). We are honored to feature Refik's work on Nifty Gateway - it is a huge moment for our platform and the NFT space.
contractObj.storeHeadline: Refik Anadol releases 5 minute open editions!

Every buyer of the Open Edition CryptoCaster will be automatically eligible to win the physical guitar. The winner will be chosen on Instagram Live (@twofeetmusic @fewocious) via a random number generator roughly 60 mins after the Open Edition ends. The corresponding NFT number will be the winner of the guitar.

 The FEWOCiOUS is an 18 year old artist, born and raised in Las Vegas, Nevada who discovered their love of art in middle school due to being bored in class. FEWOCiOUS decided to draw caricatures of their peers to pass the time. Their art has become a way for them to process growing up and serves an alternate form of journaling.  Two Feet is a platinum-certified multi-instrumentalist and recording artist from Brooklyn, New York. Streamed over 2 billion times as of 2021, triumphant on stage everywhere from Governors Ball to Austin City Limits, the #1 Alternative Radio songwriter born Bill Dess has impressively developed a massive worldwide fanbase just a few short years into his career. In addition to his musical prowess, Bill is an avid illustrator who regularly draws and paints in his spare time. Illumino is a collective of tastemakers helping artists create and collaborate in the world of digital art. Founded by crypto experts, tastemakers, and artists, Illumino is bringing highly elevated art on-chain. Illumino‚Äôs mission is to push the boundaries and possibilities in digital art while working with the best in the world to do so. We are proud to present our first official collaboration and release ‚ÄúTwo Feet x FEWOCiOUS.‚Äù

contractObj.storeDescription2: The Illumino Presents: Two Feet X FEWOCiOUS release, ‚ÄúMy Head In Your Hands‚Äù is the collaborative effort between two outstanding artists pushing the boundaries of their creative mediums. After discovering FEWOCiOUS‚Äô portfolio while exploring the world of digital art, Two Feet was captivated by their work. Serendipitously, FEWOCiOUS happened to be a long time fan of Two Feet and the two decided to collaborate on several pieces of audiovisual artwork. Two Feet wrote and recorded the music for the pieces in addition to drawing the 2d versions of the hand/head. contractObj.storeName: CHAOS by Cryptoarg
contractObj.storeDescription: Cryptoarg is a digital art collective uniting Argentinian artists of the likes of Frenetik Void, Milton Sanz, Fede Bona and Crypt0baby. This massive collaborative project brings together 23 thriving artists and their unique visions on the concept of CHAOS. CHAOS can be understood as a driving force of nature, a logic hidden deep within mathematics, a philosophy of life or a counterpoint to order and civility. Chaos is deeply rooted in all creative endeavors as a necessary energy for change. We live through and survive chaos in our daily lives, and we try to interpret it to understand the universe around us. As artists from a developing country, these creators live surrounded by chaos, sometimes struggling with it, sometimes thriving from it. Each artwork in this project is a creative interpretation with the individual perspective of each artist, creating a once in a lifetime compendium that brings a new perspective on the possibilities and perils of CHAOS. It is the biggest ever collaboration in the history of Nifty Gateway.
contractObj.storeDescription2: We are thrilled to host our largest collaboration to date. 23 artists from the digital art collective Cryptoarg decided on one word to base on their entire collection - chaos. What emotions does chaos evoke? What thoughts does chaos stimulate? Each artist had their own take on the word and it shows in each individual artwork. 23 minds came together to form one of Nifty Gateway's most exciting collections to date.
contractObj.storeHeadline: Argentinian digital art collective Cryptoarg releases collaborative pack collection!
